.TH "__remove_pages" 9 "__remove_pages" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__remove_pages \- remove sections of pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __remove_pages
.BI "(unsigned long pfn "  ","
.BI "unsigned long nr_pages "  ","
.BI "struct vmem_altmap *altmap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pfn" 12
starting pageframe (must be aligned to start of a section)
.IP "nr_pages" 12
number of pages to remove (must be multiple of section size)
.IP "altmap" 12
alternative device page map or NULL if default memmap is used
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generic helper function to remove section mappings and sysfs entries
for the section of the memory we are removing. Caller needs to make
sure that pages are marked reserved and zones are adjust properly by
calling \fBoffline_pages\fP.
